"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"49 App.:26(h) (1st sentence words before last comma, 2d, 3d sentences, 4th sentence words before last comma, last sentence).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1887-02-04/ch104"},"text":"Feb. 4, 1887, ch. 104","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/24/379"},"text":"24 Stat. 379","children":[],"tail":", § 25(h) (1st sentence words before last comma, 2d, 3d sentences, 4th sentence words before last comma, last sentence); added "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1920-02-28/ch91/s441"},"text":"Feb. 28, 1920, ch. 91, § 441","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/41/498"},"text":"41 Stat. 498","children":[],"tail":"; restated "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1937-08-26/ch818"},"text":"Aug. 26, 1937, ch. 818","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/50/837"},"text":"50 Stat. 837","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1940-09-18/ch722/s14/b"},"text":"Sept. 18, 1940, ch. 722, § 14(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/54/919"},"text":"54 Stat. 919","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"July 8, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/348/s3/d"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–348, § 3(d)","children":[],"tail":", 90 Stat 818; "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Nov. 2, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/574/s7/d"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–574, § 7(d)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/2461"},"text":"92 Stat. 2461","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Oct. 10, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/423/s8/d"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–423, § 8(d)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/1814"},"text":"94 Stat. 1814","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"June 22, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/342/s17/7"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–342, § 17(7)","children":[],"tail":", (8), "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/636"},"text":"102 Stat. 636","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Sept. 3, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/365"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–365","children":[],"tail":", §§ 4(a)(1), (c)(6), 9(a)(7), "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/973"},"text":"106 Stat. 973","children":[],"tail":", 974, 978."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"49 App.:1655(e)(1)(A), (C), (E)–(G), (K), (6)(A).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Oct. 15, 1966","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/670/s6/e/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–670, § 6(e)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", (C), (E)–(G), (K), (6)(A), "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/80/939"},"text":"80 Stat. 939","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a)(1), the words “(including but not limited to a railroad; any manager, supervisor, official, or other employee or agent of a railroad; any owner, manufacturer, lessor, or lessee of railroad equipment, track, or facilities; any independent contractor providing goods or services to a railroad; and any employee of such owner, manufacturer, lessor, lessee, or independent contractor)” are omitted as surplus because of the definition of “person” in 1:1 and because the provision being violated indicates to whom it applies. The words “violating a regulation prescribed or order issued under chapter 201 of this title related to accident and incident reporting or investigation” are substituted for “violating . . . any rule, regulation, order, or standard issued under . . . the Federal Railroad Safety Act of 1970 [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t45/s431"},"text":"45 U.S.C. 431","children":[],"tail":" et seq.] pertaining to accident reporting or investigations” in 45:43, and the words “violating chapters 203–209 of this title or a regulation or requirement prescribed or order issued under chapters 203–209” are substituted for various language in the source provisions, for clarity, for consistency in this section, and to eliminate unnecessary words. The words “liable to the United States Government for a civil penalty” are substituted for “liable to a penalty” for clarity. The text of 45:438(b) (related to 45:39) is omitted as covered by 45:43."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a)(2), the words “The Secretary of Transportation imposes a civil penalty under this subsection” are substituted for “to be assessed by the Secretary of Transportation” in 45:6, “Such penalty shall be assessed by the Secretary of Transportation” in 45:13, the text of 45:10 (words after 7th comma) and 14 (words after semicolon), and “in such amount . . . as the Secretary of Transportation deems reasonable” in 45:34 and 43 and 49 App.:26(h) for clarity and to eliminate unnecessary words. The words “per violation” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsections (a)(3) and (b), the words “Attorney General” are substituted for “United States attorney”, “such attorneys, subject to the direction of the Attorney General”, “proper United States attorney” and “proper United States attorneys” because of 28:509.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a)(3), the words “","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s3711"},"text":"section 3711 of title 31","children":[],"tail":"” are substituted for “the Federal Claims Collection Act of 1966” and “sections 3711 and 3716 to 3718 of title 31” because the Federal Claims Collection Act of 1966 has been repealed and reenacted as part of title 31 and penalties are compromised under 31:3711. In clause (B), the words “prior or subsequent” are omitted as unnecessary."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a)(4), the words “the Secretary shall refer the matter to the Attorney General for collection” are substituted for “recovered in a suit or suits to be brought by” for clarity. The words “and it shall also be the duty of the Secretary of Transportation to lodge with . . . information of any such violations as may come to his knowledge” and “and it shall be the duty of the director of locomotive inspection to give information . . . of all violations coming to his knowledge” are omitted as obsolete.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b), the words “The Attorney General shall bring a civil action in a district court of the United States to collect a civil penalty that is referred to the Attorney General for collection under subsection (a) of this section” are substituted for “and it shall be the duty of such United States attorney to bring such suits upon duly verified information being lodged with him of such violation having occurred” in 45:6, and for “It shall be the duty of such attorneys to bring such suits upon duly verified information being lodged with them showing such violations having occurred” in 49 App.:26, for clarity and consistency in this section and with other provisions of the revised title.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idcb1ddd36-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idcb1ddd37-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2008—Subsec. (a)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/432"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–432","children":[],"tail":" substituted “$25,000.” for “$10,000.” and “$100,000.” for “$20,000.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
